'''Danny Verpaele''' (born 'October 5, 1985 in [[Cocoa Beach, Florida]]) is an [[American football]] [[Safety (American football position)|free safety]] for the [[University of South Florida]] (USF) [[South Florida Bulls football|Bulls]]  [[National Collegiate Athletic Association|NCAA]] [[Division I (NCAA)|Division I]] [[college football]] team. Verpaele is a 2004 graduate of [[Merritt Island High School]].<ref>[http://www.gousfbulls.com/ViewArticle.dbml?SPSID=37330&SPID=2981&DB_OEM_ID=7700&ATCLID=216781&Q_SEASON=2008 - Danny Verpaele USF Biography <!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>

==High school==
Verpaele was a four-year [[lettermen]] for the Merritt Island Mustangs. In his junior year (2002<U+2013>2003), Verpaele led the Mustangs to the regional semifinals, losing to [[Drew Weatherford]]-led [[Land O' Lakes High School]] 20-14 on November 29, 2002. Verpaele was a Class 4A Second-Team All-State selectee in 2002. <br />
In 2003, his senior year, Verpaele erupted, passing for 1,531 yards and rushing for 1,015. Verpaele led the Mustangs to the regional final championship but they fell short, losing 27-0 to Washington High School on December 5, 2003.<ref>[http://www.fhsaa.org/fb/2003/brak4.htm - FHSAA 2003 Class 4A Football Championship <!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> Verpaele also played [[defensive back]] and was voted [[Brevard County, Florida|Brevard County]] All-[[Space Coast]] Defensive Player of the Year by the ''[[Florida Today]]''. the ''[[Orlando Sentinel]]'' voted Verpaele to its All-Central Florida team and he was ranked as the 68th Best Prospect in the state of Florida.<ref>[http://phi.scout.com/a.z?s=67&p=8&c=1&nid=3049007 - Scout.com Bio of Danny Verpaele <!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> In 2003, Verpaele was again voted to the Class 4A All-State Second Team.<ref>[http://www.maxemfingerrecruiting.com/index.php?option=content&task=view&id=68&Itemid=44 - 2003 Class 4A All-State Football teams <!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> Verpaele holds the distinction as being the first player in school history to start all four years.<ref name="phi.scout.com">[http://phi.scout.com/a.z?s=67&p=8&c=1&nid=3049007 - Verpaele First-Four year starter in school history <!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>

==College==
* 2004 - Verpaele played in 11 games his freshman year, making 25 solo [[Tackle (football move)|tackles]], 32 assisted for 57 total tackles. Verpaele also had two [[Quarterback sack|sacks]], six tackles for a loss of 13 yards, one pass break up and one [[fumble]] recovered. For his standout frosh season, Verpaele earned ''[[Sporting News]]'' Third-Team Freshman [[All-American]] honors.<ref>[http://admin.xosn.com/pdf7/83960.pdf?KEY=EJSMQTHYWNYZEKY.20070907132024&DB_ACCOUNT_TYPE=AGENT&skip_agent_menus=NO&DB_MENU_ID=286&skip_agent_info=NO&DB_LANG=C&DB_OEM_ID=7700 - Danny Verpaele 2004 USF Statistics <!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>
* 2005 - [[Redshirt (college sports)|Medical Redshirt]] (broken ankle)
* 2006 - Verpaele played in 13 games, making 26 solo tackles, 13 assisted for 39 total tackles. Verpaele recorded one tackle for a loss and recorded an [[interception]] versus the [[University of North Carolina]], returning it 26 yards. On November 25, 2006, versus No. 7 [[West Virginia University Mountaineers]], Verpaele made one of the biggest plays of the season, as he hit [[running back]] [[Steve Slaton]] on the [[Goal line (American football)|goal line]], forcing a fumble which USF recovered. The Bulls would go on to beat its then-highest ranked opponent in school history 24-19.<ref>[http://usf.rivals.com/content.asp?CID=679096 - USF.rivals.com Danny Verpaele <!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> Verpaele also recorded five tackles and broke up three passes in the Bulls bowl victory over [[East Carolina University]] in the [[PapaJohns.com Bowl]] on December 23, 2006.<ref>[http://www2.tbo.com/content/2008/aug/11/sp-verpaele-eager-to-get-back-on-field/sports-colleges-bulls/ - August 11, 2008 Verpaele Eager To Get Back On Field <!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>
* 2007 Did not play
* 2008 Senior safety for the Bulls.

==Trivia==
* Was first player in Merritt Island High School football history to start all four seasons.<ref name="phi.scout.com"/>
* Danny's older brother Kevin Verpaele (1999<U+2013>2003) was a 4-year standout for USF. Danny also wears the same jersey number (#17) Kevin wore. Kevin and Danny make just the second set of brothers to play for [[Head Coach]] [[Jim Leavitt]] (the others being [[Bill Gram<U+00E1>tica|Bill]] and [[Santiago Gram<U+00E1>tica]]).<ref>[http://www.nationalchamps.net/2003/sub/teams/southflorida.htm = Kevin Verpaele Profile <!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>

